This paper is about dialogue agents and their evaluation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on controllable neural text generation methods, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves human evaluation, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction and user studies, making cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves large-scale experiments and analysis, which suggests a focus on machine learning and statistical methods, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible sub-categories as well.
